name: StageOne Ventures Overview
overview:
StageOne Ventures, founded in 2001, is a seasoned venture capital firm investing in early-stage Israeli startups that address significant enterprise challenges through advanced technologies. With over two decades of experience, StageOne has been the first investor in many successful companies, guiding them from inception to IPOs and acquisitions, including recent exits like Qwak (acquired by JFrog), Epsagon (acquired by Cisco), Avanan (acquired by Checkpoint), and Otonomo (NSDQ: OTMO).

StageOne manages over $500M across four funds, including the latest $150M Fund IV, closed in January 2022. The firm’s portfolio includes industry leaders like Coralogix, Silverfort, NeuroBlade, and DoControl, all prominent in the enterprise-tech sector.

Specializing in preparing companies for Series A funding, StageOne works closely with both Israeli and US investors. The firm has a strong focus on Israeli founders, supporting them both in Israel and globally, including in the US and Europe.

StageOne’s investment strategy centers on three core areas: backing Israeli founders worldwide, leading seed-stage investments with follow-on support, and investing in enterprise technology across sectors like cybersecurity, software infrastructure, vertical SaaS, AI, DevOps, and Deeptech.

Based in Israel, the StageOne team includes three partners and a diverse investment team, with expertise across various domains. They provide added value services like marketing, HR, business development, corporate connections, and strategic investor introductions, helping founders achieve market leadership and build impactful companies in the enterprise tech sector.

name: OurCrowd Overview
overview:
OurCrowd is a global investment platform bringing venture capital opportunities to accredited investors worldwide. It is managed by a team of seasoned investment professionals and led by serial entrepreneur, Jon Medved.

OurCrowd vets and selects companies, invests its own capital, and invites its accredited membership of investors and institutional partners to invest alongside in these opportunities. OurCrowd provides support to its portfolio companies, assigns industry experts as mentors, and creates growth opportunities through its network of strategic multinational partnerships.

With $2.2 billion of committed funding, and investments in more than 420 portfolio companies and 50 venture funds, OurCrowd offers access to its membership of over 225,000 individual accredited and institutional investors, family offices, and venture capital partners from over 195 countries to invest alongside, at the same terms.

OurCrowd is headquartered in Jerusalem, with additional offices in Tel Aviv, New York, Abu Dhabi, Chicago, Hong Kong, London, Madrid, San Diego, São Paulo, Singapore, Toronto and Sydney.

name: iAngels Overview
overview: Founded in 2014 by Shelly Hod Moyal and Mor Assia, iAngels is a venture capital firm in Tel Aviv, Israel. Combining a deep, proprietary-research process and a uniquely curated portfolio, iAngels is committed to helping build and scale great tech companies, and has a proven ability to generate substantial returns to its investors worldwide. iAngels believes in going beyond and backs those who do, partnering with some of the highest caliber entrepreneurs in the nation. With over $550m AUM and 27 profitable exits, iAngels is one of the most active and recognized investors in the Israeli tech ecosystem.

name: General Atlantic Overview
overview: General Atlantic is a global growth equity firm with more than four decades of experience providing capital and strategic support for over 445 growth companies throughout its history. The firm combines a collaborative global approach, sector-specific expertise, a long-term investment horizon, and a deep understanding of growth drivers to partner with great entrepreneurs and management teams to scale innovative businesses around the world. General Atlantic operates across six global sectors: Climate, Consumer, Financial Services, Healthcare, Life Sciences, and Technology. General Atlantic currently has over $84 billion in assets under management inclusive of all products as of December 31, 2021, and more than 215 investment professionals based in New York, Amsterdam, Beijing, Hong Kong, Jakarta, London, Mexico City, Mumbai, Munich, Palo Alto, So Paulo, Shanghai, Singapore, Stamford and Tel Aviv.
